        "observed_type": "list_item",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A-2 We show more precisely that the game terminates with one player holding all of the pennies if and only if n = 2\" + 1 or n = 2\" + 2 for some m. First suppose we are in the following situation for some k ≥ 2. (Note: for us, a \"move\" consists of two turns, starting with a one-penny pass.)",
